 in the modified gravity model we present, the Universe is described by a\nrescaled Einstein-Hilbert gravity at early times, hence in some sense the\nmodified gravity effect is minimal primordially, and the scalar field controls\nmainly the dynamics with a rescaled Ricci scalar gravity. However $f(R)$\ngravity dominates at late-times, where it controls the dynamics,\nsynergistically with the scalar field.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 2 Dec 2020 16:31:54 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 18 May 2021 16:27:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-06-16"}
