 from the maximum of a usual GFF. More precisely, we show that with high\nprobability when $\\beta>1$ \\[ \\max_{x\\in [-n,n]^2} \\Psi_n(x) \\leq\n\\sqrt{\\frac{2\\beta}{\\pi} \\big(1 - \\beta e^{- \\frac{(2\\pi)^2\\beta} {2} } \\big)}\n\\log n \\,. \\] where $\\Psi_n$ is an integer-valued GFF in the box $[-n,n]^2$ at\ninverse temperature $\\beta^{-1}$. Applications to the free-energies of the\nCoulomb gas, the Villain model and the integer-valued GFF are also considered.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 2 Dec 2020 18:49:29 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 12 Jul 2021 15:06:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-07-13"}
