 nuclear interactions. The strong increase in the\ncharge radii beyond $N = 28$ is not well captured by these calculations, but is\nwell reproduced by Fayans nuclear density functional theory, which, however,\noverestimates the odd-even staggering effect. These findings highlight our\nlimited understanding on the nuclear size of neutron-rich systems, and expose\npressing problems that are present in some of the best current models of\nnuclear theory.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 3 Dec 2020 12:11:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-04-28"}
